---
import Base from '~/layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About — Studio Marginalia">
  <section class="page">
    <h1 class="hed serif-italic">A few things to know.</h1>
    <div class="prose serif">
      <p>I'm Nina Pfeiffer. <em>Studio Marginalia</em> is the name I write under and the name I work under — two halves of the same project, kept under one roof on purpose.</p>
      <p>This site is mostly a journal. Some weeks it's a paragraph; some months it's a 2,000-word essay. There's also a small library of <a href="/work/portfolio/">selected work</a> from the marketing side of the studio, and a <a href="/work/">page about working together</a> if you came here looking for that.</p>
      <p>I write quietly. The brief is "lived-in, not influencer-perfect." If you've found this and stuck around, I'm probably writing for you.</p>
      <p class="sig serif-italic">— Nina</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
<style>
  .page { padding: 64px 56px 96px; max-width: 64ch; margin: 0 auto; }
  .hed { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); line-height: 1.1; margin: 0 0 32px; font-weight: 400; }
  .prose { font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.75; }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 1.2em; }
  .prose em { color: var(--accent); }
  .prose a { color: var(--accent); border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--accent); }
  .sig { color: var(--accent); font-size: 22px; margin-top: 1em; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .page { padding: 40px 20px 64px; } }
</style>
